-- China Stocks: Agricultural Bank, China Pacific, Huadian Power
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-29T07:59:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-28/petrochina-jiangxi-copper-china-shipping-huadian-china-equity-preview.html
The  Shanghai Composite Index , which
tracks the bigger of China’s stock exchanges, dropped 0.2
percent to 2,866.36 at the 3 p.m. local time close. The  CSI 300
Index  declined 0.2 percent to 3,190.05.  Banks:  Industrial & Commercial Bank of China Ltd.  (601398
CH) fell 0.7 percent to 4.29 yuan, the lowest close since Oct.
29, after the Economic Observer said regulators are assessing
data from lenders to finalize new supervisory requirements.
 Agricultural Bank of China Ltd.  (601288 CH) lost 0.4 percent to
2.63 yuan.  The regulator will require lenders to maintain a minimum
overall capital adequacy ratio of 8 percent, plus 2.5 percent of
surplus capital and another countercyclical buffer of up to 2.5
percent, the Economic Observer report said.  China Pacific Insurance (Group) Co.  (601601 CH), the
nation’s third-biggest insurer, rose 1.8 percent to 23.53 yuan,
the highest close since Nov. 15. The company plans to sell its
50 percent stake in a venture with ING Groep NV for 943 million
yuan ($141 million).  Anhui Gujing Distillery Co.  (000596 CH) surged 10 percent
to 90.75 yuan, the highest close since its listing in October
1996. The company plans to raise as much as 1.3 billion yuan
from a private placement of as many as 20 million shares,
according to a statement from the Chinese liquor maker to
Shenzhen’s stock exchange.  Anhui Huamao Textile Co.  (000850 CH) rose 6.4 percent to
9.38 yuan, the biggest gain since Oct. 12, after the company
said it will invest 800 million in GF Securities Co. via a
private placement.  Henan Shuanghui Investment & Development Co.  (000895 CH), a
food producer, climbed 7.8 percent to 54.43 yuan, the highest
close since March 1. The company’s management offered to buy out
the company for 56 yuan a share. The stock resumed trading today
after being suspended on March 22.  Huadian Power International Corp . (600027 CH) advanced 2.1
percent to 3.94 yuan, the highest close since Nov. 11. The
electricity producer agreed to buy the rights to mine coal at
two pits in China for 704.5 million yuan, according to a
statement to the stock exchange on Nov. 26.  Zhejiang Jinggong Science & Technology Co.  (002006 CH)
jumped by the 10 percent daily limit to 31.96 yuan, the highest
close since at least June 2004. The machinery maker said it won
a contract to supply solar production equipment valued at 402
million yuan.  -- Irene Shen ,  Liza Lin . Editors:  Reinie Booysen , Shiyin Chen.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
